item.dc:creator: @Boreas Boreas
item.description:
@Boreas wrote:

Change
[scar]Color1=‘198465’;
Color2=‘198991’;
Color3=‘1087225’;[/scar]

to
[scar]Color1=198465;
Color2=198991;
Color3=1087225;[/scar]

When you put the ’ around the numbers, you were making them strings, when they should be integers (because findcolor needs integers). Type mismatch means a variable or constant was declared as one type, and then used in a function or whatever as another type.
